{
  "texts": [
    "Our numerical results confirm that ρ(z) remains strictly positive across all redshifts, and, consistent with the NEC, that ρ + p ≥ 0.",
    "The WEC is therefore satisfied throughout.",
    "The SEC requires both ρ + p ≥ 0 and ρ + 3p ≥ 0.While the first condition is satisfied as discussed above, we find that ρ + 3p becomes negative at low redshifts (see Figure 8).",
    "This violation of the SEC is a necessary feature for the onset of cosmic acceleration and is a common trait of accelerating cosmologies.",
    "The DEC imposes ρ ≥ 0 and ρ ≥ |p|, ensuring causal energy flow and the non-exotic character of the effective fluid."
  ]
}